JOHANNESBURG - The ANC Veterans League is calling on President Cyril Ramaphosa to act immediately against the North West Premier Supra Mahumapelo. It says the political turmoil is affecting residents. WATCH: Mahumapelo remains North West Premier Supra Mahumapelo has placed himself on leave as calls for him to step down intensify. "The president must put his foot down the public wants stability and people want quality healthcare, that’s all we are interest in,“ said Snuki Zikalala, ANC Veterans League. Mahumapelo is accused of corruption and has vowed to take aggressive legal action against those who've made the allegations. eNCA